  "notes": "Central Standard Swedish. Retroflex assimilation (⟨rd⟩→[ɖ] etc.) is characteristic of Central/Northern dialects; absent in Southern/Finland Swedish. K SOFTENING: k→[ɕ] before front vowels (ke, ki, ky, kä, kö); [k] elsewhere. G: [j] before front vowels in some positions; [ɡ] elsewhere. SK: [ɧ] (sj-sound) before front vowels; [sk] elsewhere. RETROFLEXION: /r/+coronal clusters assimilate to retroflexes (rs=[ʂ], rd=[ɖ], etc.). TONE: Swedish has two lexical tones (accent 1 = acute, accent 2 = grave). Sources: Riad (2014), Engstrand (1999), Bruce (2007).",
